cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO

This paper proposes a method for obtaining a 3D wireframe representation from a single image using a convolutional neural network. The paper focuses on computer vision and graphics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions high-level vision tasks such as AR and CAD, which further supports the likelihood of cs.CV. The paper also mentions global structural priors and the use of machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of a neural network for wireframe detection suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on 3D reconstruction suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category.
